The summer is in full swing, which means it's vacation season and time to get in the sun! For this month‚Äôs challenge, use HTML/CSS/JavaScript or Python to create a postcard of your dream vacation spot. üèñÔ∏è

Some ways to make the postcard "pop" include: captivating and visually appealing design, a suitable typography and color scheme, and a personalized message area.

Take a look at [Dribbble](https://dribbble.com/search/postcard) or [Pinterest](https://www.pinterest.com/akw518/postcard-design-inspiration) for some cool postcard ideas!

#### Challenge Rules

Be as creative as you want, but make sure to include the following tags (for HTML):

- A defined height and width for the postcard.
- At least one `<img>` image element.
- At least one `<p>` paragraph element.

**Prize:** The winner will get a physical Brooklyn postcard from the team in the mail, plus some stickers and magnets! üèÜ 

#### Submission

Post your code + screenshot in the Twitter thread (link will be posted here soon).

**Deadline:** Submit your completed postcard by **Sunday, July 30th, 2023** and it will be voted on by our Discord community. ‚è∞ 

